@page "/philosophy"

<PageTitle>Philosophy — EthicForge</PageTitle>

<div class="philosophy-hero">
    <div class="philosophy-hero__glow"></div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="philosophy-hero__content">
            <span class="badge badge--primary">Philosophy</span>
            <h1 class="philosophy-hero__title">A different approach<br /><em>to digital craftsmanship</em></h1>
            <p class="philosophy-hero__subtitle">
                EthicForge was born from a simple observation: modern technology shapes our lives,
                but too often without transparency, without respect for privacy, and without digital sovereignty.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="philosophy-intro animate-on-scroll">
            <p>
                Most digital services are built for <strong>data extraction</strong>, growth at any cost
                and dependency on foreign infrastructure. EthicForge proposes another path.
            </p>
            <p>
                Like an artisanal forge where each tool is shaped with care, we build digital applications
                according to clear and non-negotiable principles.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
        <SectionTitle Title="Our Principles"
                      Subtitle="These are not marketing promises — they are technical and ethical commitments embedded in every line of code we write."
                      Eyebrow="What we stand for" />

        <div class="principles-list">
            <div class="principle animate-on-scroll" data-delay="1">
                <div class="principle__number">01</div>
                <div class="principle__content">
                    <h3>Respect for privacy</h3>
                    <p>
                        We collect the minimum data necessary for services to function.
                        No behavioral profiling. No advertising networks. No third-party data sharing.
                        Your data belongs to you — period.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="principle animate-on-scroll" data-delay="2">
                <div class="principle__number">02</div>
                <div class="principle__content">
                    <h3>European digital sovereignty</h3>
                    <p>
                        All infrastructure is hosted in Europe and complies with French and European regulations.
                        We do not use services from companies subject to foreign intelligence laws
                        (CLOUD Act, FISA, etc.).
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="principle animate-on-scroll" data-delay="3">
                <div class="principle__number">03</div>
                <div class="principle__content">
                    <h3>Total transparency</h3>
                    <p>
                        Technical decisions and data policies are publicly documented.
                        We explain what we collect, why, for how long, and with whom it may be shared.
                        No dark patterns, no misleading design.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="principle animate-on-scroll" data-delay="4">
                <div class="principle__number">04</div>
                <div class="principle__content">
                    <h3>Independence from capital</h3>
                    <p>
                        No pressure from investment funds. No hyper-growth objectives.
                        Products are developed for their <em>utility</em> to users, not for valuation or speculation.
                        The service before the profit.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="principle animate-on-scroll" data-delay="5">
                <div class="principle__number">05</div>
                <div class="principle__content">
                    <h3>Open source when possible</h3>
                    <p>
                        Whenever possible, the code is open and documented.
                        Open source is not just a technical choice — it is an act of trust
                        and transparency toward users and the community.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="principle animate-on-scroll" data-delay="1">
                <div class="principle__number">06</div>
                <div class="principle__content">
                    <h3>Legal compliance</h3>
                    <p>
                        Full compliance with French and European law, including GDPR, DORA, and the AI Act.
                        We do not look for loopholes. We respect the spirit of the law, not just its letter.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="manifesto-block animate-on-scroll">
            <h2 class="manifesto-block__title">EthicForge is not a traditional startup.</h2>
            <p>
                It is a <strong>responsible digital creation workshop</strong>.
                A place where technology is forged with ethics.
            </p>
            <p>
                Each application developed here is conceived as a <em>durable tool</em>,
                designed to serve users — not to exploit their data.
            </p>
            <div class="manifesto-block__cta">
                <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Get in touch</a>
                <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/wishlist">See our first application</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
